izmjena:

Hardware & OS requirements:
---------------------------
Vini is the supercomputing applications and needs at least 10 computing cluster nodes to run smoothly.
Vini is tested on RHEL 7 and CENTOS 7. SLURM and SGE are supported workload managers. 

Vini is an open source program. However it uses several programs and Internet portals that are free to use for academic use but require registiration:
-----------------------------------------
Chimera registration: Go to https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/cgi-bin/chimera_registration.py and register

Installing Vini: 
----------------
Download  Vini from Github: https://github.com/draskot/Vini

Start the installiation with ./install.sh and follow the instructions. After installation is finished, execute: source sourceme

Running Vini:
--------------
Run ./vini_init and follow the instructions.


